#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/ColdFilterPluggingPoint.md:3
msgid "$$CFPP = 3.1417 \\times LCSF - 16.477$$"
msgstr "$$CFPP = 3.1417 \\times LCSF - 16.477$$"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/ColdFilterPluggingPoint.md:7
msgid "CFPP"
msgstr "CFPP"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/ColdFilterPluggingPoint.md:11
msgid "Represents the cold filter plugging point (CFPP), which is one important parameter for low temperature applications of a fuel. The CFPP is the lowest temperature at which a fuel will still flow through a specific filter before jamming it due to the formation of agglomerated crystals. It is heavily influenced by the long chain saturated factor (LCSF)."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/ColdFilterPluggingPoint.md:15
msgid "The EN 14214-2005 standard does not mention a low-temperature parameter in its specification lists. However, each country using EN 14214 can specify certain temperature limits for different times of a year depending on climate conditions."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/ColdFilterPluggingPoint.md:19
msgid "[Dunn, 2019](https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.energyfuels.9b03311 \"Correlating the Cold Filter Plugging Point to Concentration and Melting Properties of Fatty Acid Methyl Ester (Biodiesel) Admixtures\")"
msgstr "[Dunn, 2019](https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.energyfuels.9b03311 \"Correlating the Cold Filter Plugging Point to Concentration and Melting Properties of Fatty Acid Methyl Ester (Biodiesel) Admixtures\")"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/ColdFilterPluggingPoint.md:20
#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/LongChainSaturatedFactor.md:15
msgid "[Ramos _et al._, 2009](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.biortech.2008.06.039 \"Influence of fatty acid composition of raw materials on biodiesel properties\")"
msgstr "[Ramos _et al._, 2009](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.biortech.2008.06.039 \"Influence of fatty acid composition of raw materials on biodiesel properties\")"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/DegreeOfUnsaturation.md:3
msgid "$$DU = 1-UFA + 2 \\times 2-UFA + 3 \\times 3-UFA + 4 \\times 4-UFA$$"
msgstr "$$DU = 1-UFA + 2 \\times 2-UFA + 3 \\times 3-UFA + 4 \\times 4-UFA$$"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/DegreeOfUnsaturation.md:7
msgid "DU"
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/DegreeOfUnsaturation.md:11
msgid "Represents the degree of unsaturation (DU), which quantifies the total amount of double bonds present in the fatty acid profile of raw oils or biodiesel. Fuel properties such as cetane number (CN), iodine value (IV), and oxidation stability (OS) are mainly determined by the DU. When the degree of unsaturation of raw oils fatty acid is lower than 133.13, cetane number (GB/T 20828-2007) and iodine number (EN 14214) generally meet the required standards."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/IodineValue.md:3
msgid "$$IV = 0.6683 \\times DU + 25.0364$$"
msgstr "$$IV = 0.6683 \\times DU + 25.0364$$"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/IodineValue.md:7
msgid "IV"
msgstr "IV"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/IodineValue.md:11
msgid "Represents the iodine value (IV), which is an index of the number of double bonds in biodiesel. It serves as a key parameter that quantifies the degree of unsaturation (DU) of the fuel. A higher iodine value indicates a greater number of double bonds, which typically correlates with poorer oxidation stability but better cold flow properties."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/IodineValue.md:17 src/Ratio/Biodiesel/IodineValue.md:18
msgid "\\[\\-∞;120\\]"
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/LongChainSaturatedFactor.md:3
msgid "$$LCSF = 0.1 \\times C16:0 + 0.5 \\times C18:0 + 1 \\times C20:0 + 1.5 \\times C22:0 + 2 \\times C24:0$$"
msgstr "$$LCSF = 0.1 \\times C16:0 + 0.5 \\times C18:0 + 1 \\times C20:0 + 1.5 \\times C22:0 + 2 \\times C24:0$$"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/LongChainSaturatedFactor.md:7
msgid "LCSF"
msgstr "LCSF"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/LongChainSaturatedFactor.md:11
msgid "Represents the long chain saturated factor, which is used to evaluate the cold flow properties of biodiesel. It assigns increasing weight to saturated fatty acids with longer carbon chains, as they have progressively higher melting points and more severely impact the cold filter plugging point (CFPP). A higher LCSF indicates poorer cold-weather operability."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/OxidationStability.md:3
msgid "$$OS = -0.0384 \\times DU + 7.770$$"
msgstr "$$OS = -0.0384 \\times DU + 7.770$$"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/OxidationStability.md:7
msgid "OS"
msgstr "OS"

#: src/Ratio/Biodiesel/OxidationStability.md:11
msgid "Represents the oxidation stability of biodiesel, which is a critical parameter indicating the fuel's resistance to degradation upon exposure to oxygen over time. A higher oxidation stability ensures a longer shelf life and prevents the formation of gums, acids, and polymeric deposits that can clog fuel filters and damage engine components. It is inversely related to the degree of unsaturation (DU), as polyunsaturated fatty acids are highly susceptible to oxidation."
msgstr ""

