#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/SaturationIndex.md:5
msgid "$$\\frac{\\ce{C{14:0}} + \\ce{C{16:0}} + \\ce{C{18:0}}}{\\sum \\ce{UFA}}$$"
msgstr "$$\\frac{\\ce{C{14:0}} + \\ce{C{16:0}} + \\ce{C{18:0}}}{\\sum \\ce{UFA}}$$"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/SaturationIndex.md:9
msgid "SI"
msgstr "SI"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/SaturationIndex.md:10
msgid "IS"
msgstr "IS"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/SaturationIndex.md:14
msgid "Index of saturation"
msgstr "Индекс насыщения"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/SaturationIndex.md:18
msgid "Represents the saturation index, which evaluates the relationship between specific saturated fatty acids (myristic $\\ce{C{14:0}}$, palmitic $\\ce{C{16:0}}$, and stearic $\\ce{C{18:0}}$) and the sum of unsaturated fatty acids."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/SaturationIndex.md:20
msgid "From a nutritional point of view, the SI value should be as low as possible. This index serves as a straightforward indicator of the overall saturation level of the lipids in a food product. A lower SI value suggests better nutritional properties and higher lipid quality, as it reflects a higher proportion of beneficial unsaturated fatty acids relative to saturated ones. Diets with a lower saturation index are generally recommended to maintain cardiovascular health and reduce the risk of related diseases."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/ThrombogenicIndex.md:5
msgid "$$\\frac{\\ce{C{14:0}} + \\ce{C{16:0}} + \\ce{C{18:0}}}{0.5 \\times \\sum \\ce{MUFA} + 0.5 \\times \\sum \\ce{PUFA(\\omega-6)} + 3 \\times \\sum \\ce{PUFA(\\omega-3)} + \\frac{\\sum \\ce{PUFA(\\omega-3)}}{\\sum \\ce{PUFA(\\omega-6)}}}$$"
msgstr "$$\\frac{\\ce{C{14:0}} + \\ce{C{16:0}} + \\ce{C{18:0}}}{0.5 \\times \\sum \\ce{MUFA} + 0.5 \\times \\sum \\ce{PUFA(\\omega-6)} + 3 \\times \\sum \\ce{PUFA(\\omega-3)} + \\frac{\\sum \\ce{PUFA(\\omega-3)}}{\\sum \\ce{PUFA(\\omega-6)}}}$$"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/ThrombogenicIndex.md:10
msgid "IT"
msgstr "IT"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/ThrombogenicIndex.md:14
msgid "Index of thrombogenicity"
msgstr "Индекс тромбогенности"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/ThrombogenicIndex.md:15
msgid "Prothrombogenic fatty acids to antithrombogenic fatty acids ratio"
msgstr "Отношение протромбогенных жирных кислот к антитромбогенным жирным кислотам"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/ThrombogenicIndex.md:19
msgid "Represents the thrombogenic index, which characterizes the thrombogenic potential of fatty acids. It defines the ratio between prothrombogenic saturated fatty acids and antithrombogenic unsaturated fatty acids."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/ThrombogenicIndex.md:21
msgid "From a human health perspective, the TI value should be as low as possible. This index separates fatty acids into prothrombogenic ones (myristic C14:0, palmitic C16:0, and stearic C18:0), which promote clot formation in blood vessels, and antithrombogenic ones (MUFAs, n-3 and n-6 PUFAs), which prevent it. A lower TI indicates better nutritional properties of the lipids and is associated with a reduced risk of cardiovascular diseases. Furthermore, consuming foods with a lower TI can help in lowering the risk of atrial fibrillation and other heart-related conditions."
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/UnsaturationIndex.md:5
msgid "$$\\sum N \\times \\ce{NUFA}$$"
msgstr "$$\\sum N \\times \\ce{NUFA}$$"

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/UnsaturationIndex.md:9
msgid "UI"
msgstr ""

#: src/Ratio/Nutritional/UnsaturationIndex.md:13
msgid "Represents the unsaturation index, which is a measure of the number of unsaturated bonds in the fatty acid moieties of lipids (such as phospholipids). It is calculated as the fraction of each unsaturated fatty acid multiplied by the number of double bonds within that specific fatty acid. This index provides a comprehensive evaluation of the overall degree of unsaturation in a lipid sample, which is relevant for assessing membrane fluidity, oxidative stability, and nutritional quality."
msgstr ""

